<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <br>
Conclusion: Hit Points are what counts for people when fighting Fungus Beasts. My assumption is that all creatures in the same level range are going to show similar results. I have yet to parse out another creature yet though.<br>
</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Actually no they don't.<br>
<br>
Look again at the results.<br>
<br>
In all test the mob connects 40% of the time.  We can therefore conclude that Avoidance is UNCHANGED at all AC values.  This fits the hypothesis that Thresher and myself have put forward - that all avoidance is fixed based on class values.<br>
<br>
But look again at the tests, there is a change somewhere between 1080AC and 975AC.  The Avoidance stays the same but the mitigation drops and you start taking 75 damage per hit from a consistant 69 (dude!)<br>
<br>
Again this fits *exactly* the theory.  THe mob is relatively low level and the UPPER cap for the mob is somewhere around 1000AC.  AC past this level has no meaning.  For a higher mo (and other sets of parsed results show this) the AC UPPER cap will be higher.<br>
<br>
This is the point missed by those promoting the theories that there is some fixed, permanent cap.  There isn't.  There is a cap which depends on the level of mob you fight.<br>
<br>
It fits the hypothesis and it fits the empirical evidence.  That's the basis under which you can call something a Fact on scientific principles.<br>
<br>
The theory predicts more.  Keep dropping your Ac till naked.  You will find that the Avoidance doesn;'t change.  The mob will always hit 40% of the time.  but the damage per hit wil continue to rise till at some point (and given the level of mob and my experience of other mobs this will be around 800AC to 850AC) the damage per hit will STOP rising.  This is the LOWER cap.<br>
<br>
(BTW, the existance of this lower cap is what lead some people, including myself, to initially believe AC had little impact *at all* because when Rubicite was the best armour in the game, people simply couldn't get an AC high enough to get to the LOWER cap!)<br>
<br>
Your parses are good and useful but they don't give the conclusion you seem to be saying.<br>
<br>
AC is impacting here, its just only impacting at the lower end because of the low level of the mob.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
