Gjin's theorum about the Z factor is interesting and a worthwhile avenue of exploration. I feel quite certain that a mob's AC and your ATK is compared in some way to get a range of possible hits and a modal.<br>
<br>
It could also be:<br>
<br>
/random 20 - [(ATK - AC)/1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  = z<br>
<br>
or<br>
<br>
(/random 20 + ATK/10) - (/random 20 + AC/10) = x<br>
<br>
These are also rough guesses and mainly just guides for possible working formulas where the numerical values can be swapped for whatever is found to be the case.<br>
<br>
The first case seems unlikely as it would cause either:<br>
 a perfectly uniform distribution (ATK=AC) or;<br>
 a uniform distibution in a limited range with the exception of either min (AC &gt; ATK) or max (ATK &gt; AC) values which would be higher to compensate for the missing possible x values.<br>
This does not fit our working model!<br>
<br>
The second case seems more plausible but probably not the final equation, more likely a stepping stone.<br>
