<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <br>
-Parsing with and without an AGI buff, to test whether or not AC from AGI is avoidance or mitigation. I know Ed is contending that AGI is adding to mitigation only, but perhaps I'm missing something, because I'm not seeing that explicitly from the parses.<br>
</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
There is *very* little data on this.  In fact I can only think of one analysis posted to the Ranger Glade well over 18 months ago.<br>
<br>
It concluded that identical AC gains from Agility and Armour had identical results.  10AC by raising your Agility 50pts had the exact same effect on damage taken as 10AC from adding an Ac6 item.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <br>
-Maybe you all don't care, but I'm a monk, so I'm curious  I am wondering if the monk AC bonus (for being under your weight limit) is mitigation or avoidance. Could be tested by parsing at different carried weights.<br>
</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
You're making the assumption that the negative effect of being overweight is actually tied to the gains Monks get from being Monks.  That may or may not be the case but whether it is or not it strikes me as a dangerous assumption.<br>
<br>
I expect it to be 100% Avoidance because we can see empirically that Monks get hit less.  That's what seperates them.<br>
<br>
In any case it doesn't *matter* because it is a fixed value the player can't effect.  And as we can see more and more clearly the &quot;concepts&quot; of Avoidance and Mitigation are UTTERLY IRRELEVANT.  Because a player can only ever effect Mitigation.  So AC is AC is AC in terms of what a character can do to effect their toon.<br>
