<br>
I think that STR and ATK is what determines the frequency and amount of hits higher than mode. The generally accepted rule is that below level 20, a melee cannot hit for more than mode. This isn't actually the case. I noticed it first on my ogre warrior when he was level 18 or so, but he was hitting higher than that. With HoS and a STR buff stacked, he had 255 STR. He was hitting for 36 max with a 17 damage 2 hander. That is 2 more than the modal hit. He had those same buffs at earlier levels, but wasn't hitting higher than mode. I attribute that to the increase in atk from offense and weapon skill increases. I did not see hits higher than mode without the buffs however. <br>
